item.title: [JDK-8240567] MethodTooLargeException thrown while creating a jlink image
item.description:
ADDITIONAL SYSTEM INFORMATION :
Centos 6/7/8, Ubuntu 16/18.04, Windows 10
Java 11.0.3, Java 12.0.1, Java 13

A DESCRIPTION OF THE PROBLEM :
When producing a JLink Image the tool exceptions out with the ASM bug of MethodTooLarge.
This occurs when using a large module-info spec.
Hibernate, CXF, and Rest Services have a fairly large modular-spec

STEPS TO FOLLOW TO REPRODUCE THE PROBLEM :
Create a modular project with the following dependencies -
```
        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.guicedee.services</groupId>
            <artifactId>apache-poi</artifactId>
<version>1.0.2.18-jre13</version>
        </dependency>

        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.guicedee.services</groupId>
            <artifactId>apache-poi-ooxml</artifactId>
<version>1.0.2.18-jre13</version>
        </dependency>

<dependency>
            <groupId>com.guicedee.servlets</groupId>
            <artifactId>guiced-swagger</artifactId>
<version>1.0.2.18-jre13</version>
        </dependency>
```

```
module break.it {
   requires org.apache.poi;
    requires org.apache.poi.ooxml;
    requires com.guicedee.services.swaggerui;

}
```

EXPECTED VERSUS ACTUAL BEHAVIOR :
EXPECTED -
Build a jlink Image
ACTUAL -

item.summary: MethodTooLargeException thrown while creating a jlink image

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
JDK 21u Fix Request (Retrospective)

Low risk fix. jlink fails when linking a large number of modules as the generated method exceeds 65k limit.

A pull request was submitted for review.
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk21u/pull/65
Date: 2023-08-16 18:19:12 +0000

Changeset: ec7da91b
Author: Oliver Kopp <kopp.dev@gmail.com>
Committer: Mandy Chung <mchung@openjdk.org>
Date: 2023-07-06 16:08:36 +0000
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/commit/ec7da91bd83803b7d91a4de3a01caf0ba256c037

Copied Oliver's reply from https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/14408#issuecomment-1591903575

I don't have a bugs.openjdk.org account; thus I reply here.

The constant pool is also an "interesting" limitation. We did not address it (yet) because the current patch is IMHO a major step forward: It unblocks feature development of our software: We can add new external libraries

Looking more close to that limit and the implications to the patch: I understand that this limit affects the number of methods in a class. If this is correct, let's assume that a project requires thousands of modules and would use half of the limit for the generation of the module descriptors. That would result in roughly 32,000 methods. The patch puts 50 module descriptors in one method. Assuming 32,000 methods leads to ~1.6 million modules for a Java program.

Currently, our project JabRef has a total number of ~130 modules. We cannot move forward with our release as we cannot add new dependencies. We hope that other projects with many modules will benefit from this patch as well.

A pull request was submitted for review.
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/14408
Date: 2023-06-11 21:01:54 +0000
In JDK 21 MethodTooLargeException is not thrown (see JDK-8308477 and JDK-8308549), however the problem remains.

A pull request was submitted for review.
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/10704
Date: 2022-10-13 21:15:16 +0000
Thanks for the reproducer, the issue is clear now. The system modules plugin needs to split up the initialisation of the module descriptors array to keep the method size under 64k.

The observation on Windows 10 with https://github.com/GedMarc/JDK_Jlink_Bug:
JDK 13 Fail. Error: jdk.internal.org.objectweb.asm.MethodTooLargeException: Method too large

ILW=MML=P4

New reproducer from the submitter:
https://github.com/GedMarc/JDK_Jlink_Bug
Replicating by using mvn install

I can see how this might happen but surprised the method size is anywhere here the limit. The project attached to the issue doesn't build. Is there a version that doesn't depend on the parent POM? Alternatively would it be possible to attach the class file for jdk.internal.module.SystemModules$all.
Informed the submitter the observations and requested more information of reproducing the issue.

The observations on Windows 10:
JDK 11: Pass. Built image successfully.
JDK 12: Pass. Built image successfully.
JDK 13: Pass. Built image successfully.
